<item>
            <title>[LU-18986] Target registration to handle large amount of NIDs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18986</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For upcoming features like multi-tenancy, target registration protocol have to handle large amount of NIDs passed to MGS, e.g. with 128 vlans and 4 interfaces on each that requires 512 NIDs to be passed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current limit is about 37 NIDs only, that is how many can fit in request buffer when NIDs are passed as inline &lt;tt&gt;mti_nidlist[]&lt;/tt&gt; buffer in &lt;tt&gt;struct mgs_target_info&lt;/tt&gt;.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Main idea is to use bulk protocol when amount of NIDs is big and stick with inline buffer when NIDs fits in it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
